translated: Carlström, Sven Harald was a district clerk from Mölndal. He was born on November 27, 1894 in Falun to factory worker Fredrik C. and Sofia Carlström. He married Edith Lundgren in 1919 and they had three children: Ulla (born in 1920), Göran (born in 1923), Esbjörn (born in 1926), and Ulf (born in 1929). He passed his high school graduation exam in Falun in 1915 and then traveled to France, Italy, Germany, and Belgium in 1938. He worked at the National Police Board in Jönköping from 1919 to 1939, as a district clerk in Skellefteå from 1939 to 1946, and in Mölndal since 1946. He was chairman of the YMCA in Skellefteå from 1940 to 1946, chairman of the taxpayers association in Västerbotten from 1940 to 1945, vice-chairman of the rent tribunal from 1942 to 1946, chairman and crown ombudsman of the taxpayers association since 1920, and church commissioner in Skellefteå from 1943 to 1946.
